---

## Agent Roles

### Architect Agent
Transforms abstract concepts into structured system blueprints.

### Builder Agent
Converts blueprint logic into deployable assets (code, landing pages, APIs).

### Optimizer Agent
Identifies structural inefficiencies and revenue leaks.

### Revenue Agent
Implements pricing logic, funnel architecture, and offer positioning.

---

## Installation

### 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/intotheunknownfearlessly/manus.git
cd manus
````

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

or

```bash
pnpm install
```

### 3. Configure Environment

Copy environment template:

```bash
cp configs/env.example .env
```

Fill required variables:

```
OPENAI_API_KEY=
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
```

---

## Local Execution

```bash
npm run dev
```

Production build:

```bash
npm run build
npm run start
```

---

## Deployment

Supported environments:

* Vercel
* Supabase Edge Functions
* Docker (containerized execution)
* Local sovereign execution

Example (Vercel):

```bash
vercel deploy
```

---

## Monetization Layer

MANUS embeds monetization directly in:

* Offer generation
* Funnel architecture
* Subscription logic
* One-time digital product releases
* AI-powered premium tooling

It is designed to allow:

* High-ticket product releases
* Automated micro-offers
* AI-generated digital product kits
* Agent-run launch sequences

